%C A110877 5^n = (n-th row terms) dot (first n+1 terms in the series (1, 4, 7, 10, ...)). Example for row 4: 5^4 = 625 = (21, 58, 37, 10, 1) dot (1, 4, 7, 10, 13) = (21 + 232 + 259 + 100 + 13). - _Gary W. Adamson_, Jun 15 2011
